        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-05-17T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-05-17T16:00:00-05:00" n="1292" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1292">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.8573/5–1249: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-05-17T17:00:00-04:00">May 17, 1949—5 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>955. Dept considers inadvisable defend against or resist large-scale armed
                    aggression by counter-use firearms (urtel 1611 May 12). Primary purpose arming
                    American civilian and Marine guards inhibit or discourage violation premises.
                    Decision arm American guards left discretion officer in charge. Classified
                    material and equipment should be destroyed when necessary rather than
                    defended.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
